Reasoning: The paper deals with finding good representations of systems of XOR-constraints for use in SAT solving, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also uses methods from circuit complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) to prove lower bounds. Additionally, the paper discusses the class of propagation-complete clause-sets, which is related to the study of logic and proof theory (cs.LO) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
